This paper is about unsupervised visual representation learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of contrastive learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks to learn representations, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions detection and segmentation tasks, which are subfields of natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively.
